{
  "texts": [
    "One promising approach is retrieval-augmented generation (RAG), in which the language model works with external, reliable sources in addition to its trained world knowledge (Gao et al., 2024; Ovadia et al., 2024).",
    "Domain-specific fine-tuning on curated specialist data has also proven useful to focus the model on consistent and verifiable knowledge.",
    "In addition, a downstream fact check-using hybrid AI-human workflows (Borghoff et al., 2025) or manual-will further ensure the correctness of the content.",
    "Farquhar et al. (2024) present another promising statistics-based approach, proposing entropy-based uncertainty estimators for large language models to detect a specific type of hallucination known as confabulations.",
    "Unlike traditional methods that focus on word sequences, this approach measures uncertainty at the semantic level, recognizing that a single idea can be conveyed through different phrasings."
  ]
}